cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "agent-gorgon: tool-fabrication defense for AI agents"
abstract: >-
  agent-gorgon is an AI reliability tool that stops AI agents from fabricating
  tool output when a registered tool exists, using a three-layer Claude Code
  hook defense (UserPromptSubmit, Stop, and a PreToolUse Bash matcher). It is
  verification by effect against a silent failure mode that evals and
  observability miss: confabulated output indistinguishable from real tool
  results.
type: software
version: 0.1.0
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/hermes-labs-ai/agent-gorgon"
url: "https://hermes-labs.ai"
keywords:
  - AI reliability
  - LLM reliability
  - silent failure modes
  - verification by effect
  - tool-fabrication detection
  - claude-code hooks
  - agent tool-use enforcement
  - anti-confabulation
